freenet.node.fcp
Class FCPClient

java.lang.Object
  freenet.node.fcp.FCPClient

public class FCPClient
extends Object

An FCP client. Identified by its Name which is sent on connection. Tracks persistent requests for either PERSISTENCE_REBOOT or PERSISTENCE_FOREVER. Note that anything that modifies a non-transient field on a PERSISTENCE_FOREVER client should be called in a transaction. Hence the addition of the ObjectContainer parameter to all such methods.

queuePendingMessagesOnConnectionRestart

public void queuePendingMessagesOnConnectionRestart(FCPConnectionOutputHandler outputHandler,
                                                    com.db4o.ObjectContainer container)
Queue any and all pending messages from already completed, unacknowledged, persistent requests, to be immediately sent. This happens automatically on startup and hopefully will encourage clients to acknowledge persistent requests!
